Single-session tickets for the U.S. Gymnastics Championships August 18-21 at Amalie Arena in Tampa are now on sale. Multi-session packages also are available. The four-day event will determine all-around and individual apparatus champions across the junior and senior men’s and women’s divisions. The U.S. men’s and women’s national teams will be renamed following the competition. Reigning U.S. men’s all-around champion Brody Malone will attempt to defend his title and a new champion will be crowned on the women’s side, as participants begin the path to the Paris Olympic Games in 2024. Multiple Olympians and world medalists are expected to compete. Here is the tentative competition schedule, which is subject to change: Thursday, Aug. 18 and Saturday, Aug. 20: Men’s gymnastics — juniors, 1:30 p.m.; seniors, 7 Friday, Aug. 19 and Sunday, Aug. 21: Women’s gymnastics — juniors, 1:30 p.m.; seniors, 7 Tickets can be purchased at Ticketmaster.com. Advanced parking passes are available at ParkWhiz.com. Visit amaliearena.com or call 813-301-2500 for more information.